	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sik's answer is convincing. But should that apply to works of fiction? <br /><br />case 1: band of brothers/the pacific: the red cross is accurately represented as an organization providing aid.<br />case 2: doom: first aid kits may be a discoursive slip, but then it's also hell on mars.<br /><br />maybe worse that doom in terms of representation: sexy nurse halloween costumes?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


